BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (09): SWITZERLAND (BERN) CATTLE, BTV-8, OIE
***************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 18 Sep 2019 (published)
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2019; 32(38) [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31775


Bluetongue, Switzerland
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 17 Sep 2019 from Mr. Hans Wyss, Chief Veterinary Officer, Schwarzenburgstrasse 161, Swiss Federal Veterinary Office, LIEBEFELD BERNE, Switzerland

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 13 Sep 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 16 Sep 2019
Report date: 16 Sep 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 17 Sep 2019
Reason for notification Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Dec 2018
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 8
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1 (BT_2019_BE_1): Oberbalm, Oberbalm, Bern-Mittelland, Bern
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Sep 2019
Outbreak status: Resolved (16 Sep 2019)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 63 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The 6-month-old bull was tested for bluetongue in the frame of a health check performed to prepare its sale. The animal is healthy and has not shown any symptoms of disease.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; zoning; control of vectors; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: No other measures

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Bluetongue (BT), an OIE-listed, vector-borne, non-zoonotic orbivirus disease, is seasonal, synchronic with the seasonality of the relevant _Culicoides_ vectors. The current case heralds the commencement of the new season. It remains to be seen if additional such cases will follow.

Switzerland's most recent BTV-8 event took place in late 2017, starting 19 Oct 2017 and declared as resolved on 31 Dec 2018. See its OIE summary with a map presenting the 93 outbreaks at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=25166. - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Bern, Switzerland: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6684882,51749]
